form.text:
Put bowls of water near where your
cat frequently spends its time. It helps to use clear, wide glass bowls that will interest your cat!

Cats dislike water that's been stagnant for a long time, and it's not healthy for them. 
Give them fresh water at least twice a day.
Dry cat food is cheap and nutritious, but it doesn’t have much moisture. Kitties that don't drink much water should have wet food containing plenty of moisture.
